<br>
    Today my partner and I were hunting the sisters in Lesser Fay, when a gnome promptly sat down in front of us.  I play a pure teamer (on Vallon Zek), and tell her it would be wise if she left this place.  She didn't say anything so my partner and I killed her.  She runs and grabs her corpse, and sits down in front of us again.  I tell her to scoot twice, backstab her, tell her again, then she goes afk.<br>
<br>
       HERES my problem.  We killed her again.  Call it what you will, but she was warned twice before she went afk.  She threatened to petition, then I started talking to her guildmaster.  He told me they did loot and scoot, but said because she was killed dishonorably that she didn't have too.  He wouldn't believe that we killed her BEFORE she went afk the first time, so the problem went unresolved, and he actually told me that I was on the verge of becoming kos.  I gave up arguing, and left the zone.<br>
<br>
        Was I wrong to kill her when she went afk?  I'm unaware that its petitionable, and I even threatened her twice before she did it!  Also, was I wrong in inquiring the rules of her guild?  I know that a few bad apples can really ruin a guilds name, so I was just making sure.  So now I am kos to a guild because they won't listen to reasoning, or screenshots.<br>
<br>
Ahh, life on Vallon.  Just another day..  =)<br>
<br>
Delduwath, rogue of the 13th season.<br>
